{
  "texts": [
    "Alzubaidi et al. (2023) explained ways and tools to deal with the challenge of data scarcity.",
    "AD is a multifactorial disease, and integrating various biomarkers, including genetic, neuroimaging, and biochemical markers improves the prediction accuracy.",
    "To this end, El-Sappagh et al. (2021a) demonstrates the use of multimodal data that involves neuroimaging, clinical and genetic data.",
    "In conclusion, addressing these facets-enhancing biomarkers, leveraging neuroimaging, incorporating cognitive and clinical data, integrating multimodal data constitutes the pathway to refining and advancing the prediction of AD progression.",
    "Data scarcity is a major challenge in deep learning, and it has particularly serious effects on CAD models used to diagnose AD."
  ]
}